17
00:00:12,297 --> 00:00:12,414
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,415 --> 00:00:15,415
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,439 --> 00:00:20,733
<i>Pursued by pirates!</i>

20
00:00:20,775 --> 00:00:22,193
<i>While on a rite of passage,</i>

21
00:00:22,276 --> 00:00:26,113
<i>six Jedi younglings and Ahsoka Tano
are ambushed.</i>

22
00:00:26,197 --> 00:00:30,910
<i>Protecting the young Jedi, Ahsoka was
captured by the nefarious Hondo Ohnaka</i>

23
00:00:30,952 --> 00:00:33,287
<i>and taken to the planet Florrum.</i>

24
00:00:33,412 --> 00:00:35,498
<i>Marshaling their courage and training,</i>

25
00:00:35,581 --> 00:00:40,419
<i>the younglings infiltrated
the pirate stronghold and rescued Ahsoka.</i>

26
00:00:40,503 --> 00:00:45,841
<i>Now we find our heroes in a race to
their stars hip, with the pirates closing in.</i>

27
00:01:00,022 --> 00:01:02,817
I know. I see them. They're gaining on us!

28
00:01:10,408 --> 00:01:11,450
Uh...

29
00:01:11,534 --> 00:01:13,828
I think they're still upset
that we tricked them.

30
00:01:18,332 --> 00:01:20,543
They'll get over it
once we're off their planet.

31
00:01:23,879 --> 00:01:25,506
I wouldn't be so sure about that.

32
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:26,632
Right!

33
00:01:26,716 --> 00:01:28,759
Ganodi, we need a quick evac.

34
00:01:28,843 --> 00:01:30,136
Come in, please.

35
00:01:30,219 --> 00:01:31,387
Ganodi!

36
00:01:31,470 --> 00:01:33,347
Uh, maybe the pirates
are jamming the signal.

37
00:01:33,639 --> 00:01:35,725
Where could she be?

38
00:01:35,808 --> 00:01:38,060
Ganodi ! Huyang ! Come in!

39
00:01:43,232 --> 00:01:46,444
Attaching your head
took a lot longer than I thought it would.

40
00:01:46,527 --> 00:01:48,404
It is appreciated, youngling.

41
00:01:48,487 --> 00:01:51,073
Mobility is paramount,
especially in an emergency.

42
00:01:51,157 --> 00:01:52,700
<i>Ganodi! Where are you?</i>

43
00:01:53,659 --> 00:01:56,245
I'm here. I was in the back fixing Huyang.

44
00:01:56,329 --> 00:01:57,496
<i>Great! That's great!</i>

45
00:01:57,580 --> 00:02:00,416
But we're all gonna need repairs
if you don't have the engines running!

46
00:02:00,499 --> 00:02:02,126
<i>- Where are you?</i>
- Ganodi.

47
00:02:02,209 --> 00:02:03,753
It's Ahsoka.

48
00:02:03,836 --> 00:02:06,464
Padawan Tano!
We rescued you!

49
00:02:06,589 --> 00:02:10,134
Almost, but we need you to get us home.
Are you ready?

50
00:02:10,217 --> 00:02:12,011
<i>Just tell me what I need to do.</i>

51
00:02:12,094 --> 00:02:15,222
Okay, fire up the engines
and head to these coordinates.

52
00:02:15,306 --> 00:02:16,682
We'll be right there!

53
00:02:41,999 --> 00:02:43,501
- There they are!
- Artoo.

54
00:02:43,584 --> 00:02:46,170
Hold her steady
and lower the boarding ramp.

55
00:02:48,714 --> 00:02:50,007
Come on!

56
00:03:06,691 --> 00:03:08,442
Looks like our ride is here.

57
00:03:08,526 --> 00:03:10,861
Everyone, get top side and stay down.

58
00:03:13,239 --> 00:03:15,658
But who's going to pilot the tank?

59
00:03:16,701 --> 00:03:18,869
Katooni, grab that mask!

60
00:03:21,163 --> 00:03:24,291
Uh, that'll have to do.

61
00:03:41,892 --> 00:03:43,394
The steering must have come loose!

62
00:03:51,902 --> 00:03:53,112
We got him!

63
00:03:54,572 --> 00:03:55,740
Hang on!

64
00:04:01,370 --> 00:04:02,747
Oh, no.

65
00:04:04,331 --> 00:04:06,751
No! No! No!

66
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:24,226
They're coming back!

67
00:04:44,872 --> 00:04:47,458
Artoo, get out of there now!

68
00:04:51,295 --> 00:04:53,631
Everyone, let go!

69
00:04:53,714 --> 00:04:54,882
Jump down now!

70
00:04:57,051 --> 00:04:59,220
Abandon ship!

71
00:05:14,819 --> 00:05:17,446
Nice try, little Jedi,

72
00:05:17,571 --> 00:05:20,241
but it looks like you're coming with us.

73
00:05:36,507 --> 00:05:38,008
What the...

74
00:05:39,260 --> 00:05:40,970
Droids?

75
00:05:42,429 --> 00:05:44,765
It's an invasion.

76
00:06:05,494 --> 00:06:06,704
Boss! Boss!

77
00:06:07,955 --> 00:06:09,832
We're all in trouble!

78
00:06:18,966 --> 00:06:20,634
Hondo!

79
00:06:20,718 --> 00:06:23,637
General Grievous, I presume?

80
00:06:23,721 --> 00:06:24,805
What a surprise.

81
00:06:25,472 --> 00:06:26,682
Have a seat.

82
00:06:26,807 --> 00:06:28,809
What may I ask is the honor?

83
00:06:30,394 --> 00:06:33,689
You can dispense
with the pleasantries, pirate.

84
00:06:33,814 --> 00:06:37,359
This planet is now under
Separatist control.

85
00:06:37,484 --> 00:06:38,652
Uh-huh.

86
00:06:39,403 --> 00:06:41,989
And what do you suppose that means?

87
00:06:42,031 --> 00:06:46,201
It means you have a new master,
pirate scum.

88
00:06:52,499 --> 00:06:55,836
<i>Hondo Ohnaka, we meet again.</i>

89
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,714
<i>As I recall,
the last time we met face-to-face,</i>

90
00:06:58,839 --> 00:07:04,511
<i>I was your prisoner and you attempted to
barter me off to the highest bidder.</i>

91
00:07:04,553 --> 00:07:05,679
But can you blame me?

92
00:07:05,721 --> 00:07:09,558
I mean, a Sith Lord,
what a handsome price you would catch...

93
00:07:09,683 --> 00:07:10,726
<i>Silence!</i>

94
00:07:10,851 --> 00:07:13,729
<i>You are going to
pay the price for your treachery.</i>

95
00:07:13,854 --> 00:07:15,522
Well, I'm a reasonable man.

96
00:07:15,606 --> 00:07:17,608
Name the price.
I'm sure we can reach an equitable...

97
00:07:17,691 --> 00:07:21,528
<i>There will be payment,
but no deals, only demands.</i>

98
00:07:21,612 --> 00:07:24,406
<i>Your entire arsenal will be melted down.</i>

99
00:07:24,531 --> 00:07:29,954
<i>Everything you own
is now property of the Separatist Alliance.</i>

100
00:07:30,037 --> 00:07:31,538
Now you go too far!

101
00:07:31,622 --> 00:07:33,123
Unacceptable!

102
00:07:33,207 --> 00:07:35,250
This is an outrage! This...

103
00:07:35,376 --> 00:07:38,420
Hold on... We can make a deal. Wait, wait!

104
00:07:38,545 --> 00:07:41,548
This is not good business!

105
00:07:42,383 --> 00:07:43,884
This isn't good.

106
00:07:43,968 --> 00:07:46,887
Those scrappin' droids
are looting the place!

107
00:07:46,971 --> 00:07:48,931
They're dismantling our ships!

108
00:07:49,056 --> 00:07:51,266
The fact that Grievous is here
with his entire fleet

109
00:07:51,392 --> 00:07:54,395
means that Master Kenobi
must have been overrun.

110
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:57,898
This entire system
is now in Separatist controlled space.

111
00:07:58,023 --> 00:08:00,567
What should we do?
There's nowhere to run.

112
00:08:00,693 --> 00:08:05,072
You're not running anywhere, scug.
You're still my prisoner.

113
00:08:05,197 --> 00:08:10,035
Maybe I can trade you to the Separatists
in exchange for my freedom.

114
00:08:10,077 --> 00:08:11,620
Not likely.

115
00:08:11,745 --> 00:08:14,039
Grievous didn't come here to make deals.

116
00:08:14,081 --> 00:08:16,750
He already controls
the planet and the system.

117
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:20,421
If you hand us over to him,
he'll kill us and then you.

118
00:08:20,546 --> 00:08:24,800
We have a common enemy in Grievous.
Together, we can get out of this.

119
00:08:24,925 --> 00:08:26,927
You must have
some other ships somewhere.

120
00:08:26,969 --> 00:08:28,220
You are pirates.

121
00:08:28,262 --> 00:08:33,142
Hondo's got a private fleet,
but only he knows where those ships are.

122
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:35,436
Then we'll have to rescue him.

123
00:08:36,061 --> 00:08:38,731
I know Grievous, and I know droids.

124
00:08:38,772 --> 00:08:42,067
With my help, you stand a better chance.

125
00:08:49,742 --> 00:08:52,786
You got yourself a deal, Jedi.

126
00:09:09,303 --> 00:09:10,471
Halt!

127
00:09:12,806 --> 00:09:14,641
You captured this tank?

128
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:16,810
Not bad for an astromech.

129
00:09:18,479 --> 00:09:20,314
What's your ID number?

130
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:24,818
Hey!

131
00:09:24,943 --> 00:09:28,781
Do not get smart with me. I outrank you.

132
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:35,329
You just watch yourself.

133
00:09:35,454 --> 00:09:38,332
I could have you melted down
with the rest of this junk.

134
00:09:38,499 --> 00:09:40,459
That's right.

135
00:09:40,501 --> 00:09:43,003
Now, take it over to Hangar 12.

136
00:09:44,296 --> 00:09:47,841
And no detours. We'll be watching you.

137
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:14,368
Jedi, and here I thought
you made your escape, no?

138
00:10:14,493 --> 00:10:17,704
No, there were complications.

139
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:20,999
Now we have to put our differences aside
and be friends,

140
00:10:21,041 --> 00:10:23,043
or else we're all going to die here.

141
00:10:23,085 --> 00:10:24,169
Ah.

142
00:10:24,211 --> 00:10:26,547
Very diplomatic.

143
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:30,008
I knew you did not come back
to rescue Hondo,

144
00:10:30,050 --> 00:10:33,554
how do you say it,
"Out of the goodness of your hearts?"

145
00:10:33,595 --> 00:10:34,930
No, no, no, no.

146
00:10:35,055 --> 00:10:37,891
You need something from me.

147
00:10:38,016 --> 00:10:40,435
-A ship, to be specific.
-Ah!

148
00:10:40,561 --> 00:10:42,563
Yes, a ship, a ship.

149
00:10:43,522 --> 00:10:46,191
But where would we find one of those?

150
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:49,945
My new friend General Grievous
has destroyed my ships.

151
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:52,739
We know you have one,
a whole pirate fleet!

152
00:10:53,907 --> 00:10:58,370
And one of my old friends, apparently,
has been talking too much.

153
00:10:59,746 --> 00:11:01,748
Ah ! What does it matter?

154
00:11:01,874 --> 00:11:06,086
We'll never reach the vault anyway.
Grievous's army is way too big.

155
00:11:06,128 --> 00:11:08,088
Don't give up. We can fight!

156
00:11:08,213 --> 00:11:13,385
If I may, sir, I have instructed younglings
for over a thousand generations,

157
00:11:13,427 --> 00:11:16,221
and these
are among the best I have ever seen.

158
00:11:17,097 --> 00:11:19,308
Well, then, show me.

159
00:11:19,433 --> 00:11:22,603
Show me your swords, tiny Jedi.

160
00:11:22,644 --> 00:11:26,106
Show Hondo you are ready to fight.

161
00:11:27,608 --> 00:11:28,650
Ah.

162
00:11:28,775 --> 00:11:31,278
And you, child, where is your saber?

163
00:11:32,112 --> 00:11:33,822
It's not finished.

164
00:11:33,947 --> 00:11:35,073
I never finished it.

165
00:11:35,115 --> 00:11:37,826
I've done everything right,
but it won't work!

166
00:11:37,951 --> 00:11:39,286
You must trust that

167
00:11:39,411 --> 00:11:43,665
the components that form your lightsaber
are meant to be together.

168
00:11:43,790 --> 00:11:45,292
There is no other way.

169
00:11:45,417 --> 00:11:47,836
It is the Force that binds them.

170
00:11:47,961 --> 00:11:51,632
Yes, I was just going to say that.
Finish it now. Finish. Finish.

171
00:11:51,757 --> 00:11:54,301
This is worth the price of a ship.

172
00:11:54,426 --> 00:11:59,014
To see the construction of
a Jedi lightsaber, this...

173
00:11:59,139 --> 00:12:00,515
This is priceless!

174
00:12:00,641 --> 00:12:05,103
Finish it, and together,
we can defeat Grievous.

175
00:12:12,945 --> 00:12:15,447
Oh, amazing !

176
00:12:19,493 --> 00:12:21,662
That is truly amazing.

177
00:12:29,503 --> 00:12:33,173
Well, cut me down, little Jedi.
It's time to leave.

178
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,848
-Look at that!
-So exciting!

179
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:43,308
So, why the big show?

180
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:47,354
You didn't really have a choice.
You know we have to work together.

181
00:12:47,479 --> 00:12:52,859
Because, Jedi, you know what
we are about to attempt is very dangerous,

182
00:12:53,652 --> 00:12:59,700
and I may be a pirate,
but I do not like taking children into battle.

183
00:12:59,825 --> 00:13:02,369
That didn't seem to bother you
when you attacked us.

184
00:13:04,162 --> 00:13:09,376
Well, today is a new day,
and lucky for you, today, I like children.

185
00:13:09,501 --> 00:13:12,004
Now, let's free the rest of my men.

186
00:13:34,526 --> 00:13:36,361
<i>This is OOM-87, General.</i>

187
00:13:36,403 --> 00:13:41,241
<i>The prison area is under attack.
There are several miniature Jedi here.</i>

188
00:13:41,283 --> 00:13:45,579
What? You aren't making any sense.
What Jedi?

189
00:13:45,704 --> 00:13:50,042
<i>Little ones, half the size of a normal Jedi.
They're freeing the prisoners and...</i>

190
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:51,209
<i>My knees!</i>

191
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:54,421
Ah!

192
00:13:54,546 --> 00:13:56,256
Prepare to open fire.

193
00:13:56,381 --> 00:13:58,925
We will bring the building down
on their heads.

194
00:14:48,809 --> 00:14:49,810
I got your back.

195
00:14:49,935 --> 00:14:52,854
Great. I feel so safe.

196
00:15:10,163 --> 00:15:11,832
They run.

197
00:15:11,873 --> 00:15:13,333
Quickly, after them!

198
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,211
They went the wrong way!

199
00:15:58,295 --> 00:16:00,046
Don't worry.

200
00:16:23,487 --> 00:16:26,573
What about the others?
We can't just leave them.

201
00:16:26,656 --> 00:16:29,242
You are welcome to come, small one.

202
00:16:29,326 --> 00:16:32,245
You may join our merry band of pirates.

203
00:16:32,329 --> 00:16:34,164
I won't just run away.

204
00:16:34,247 --> 00:16:37,667
Ahsoka trusted you. We all trusted you.

205
00:16:50,430 --> 00:16:52,724
Artoo, do something !

206
00:16:52,807 --> 00:16:55,268
I don't know.
We have to shake Grievous off.

207
00:16:55,352 --> 00:16:57,062
Get aggressive. Ah!

208
00:17:12,869 --> 00:17:16,206
Too aggressive. Far too aggressive.

209
00:17:16,289 --> 00:17:17,457
Whoa!

210
00:17:24,214 --> 00:17:29,219
Yes, well, it was an effective strategy,
but not what I would recommend.

211
00:17:53,159 --> 00:17:57,497
So many lightsabers
to add to my collection.

212
00:18:08,758 --> 00:18:09,843
Hurry!

213
00:18:09,926 --> 00:18:11,011
Come on!

214
00:18:11,094 --> 00:18:12,596
Run.

215
00:18:12,679 --> 00:18:14,681
All of you, run!

216
00:18:47,756 --> 00:18:49,049
Ha!

217
00:19:07,859 --> 00:19:10,737
-Ahsoka, come on !
-Come on, Ahsoka!

218
00:19:17,077 --> 00:19:20,246
You will never defeat Grievous.

219
00:19:20,372 --> 00:19:23,583
Never!

220
00:19:23,667 --> 00:19:25,877
I wouldn't be so sure.

221
00:19:29,756 --> 00:19:31,091
Did we get him?

222
00:19:31,216 --> 00:19:32,842
I can't tell.

223
00:19:38,431 --> 00:19:41,184
Show's over, kiddies. Let's get out of here.

224
00:20:07,836 --> 00:20:09,254
And let me see...

225
00:20:09,337 --> 00:20:13,675
Oh, the cost of the fuel.
I had to use a lot of fuel.

226
00:20:13,758 --> 00:20:17,095
The general wear and tear
on my men and equipment.

227
00:20:17,178 --> 00:20:20,265
A couple of them died, I think.

228
00:20:20,348 --> 00:20:26,187
Believe me, Kenobi, staging a rescue
is not an inexpensive proposition.

229
00:20:26,271 --> 00:20:29,649
So you mean to tell me
you were staging a rescue,

230
00:20:29,733 --> 00:20:32,444
not attempting to hijack a Jedi stars hip?

231
00:20:32,527 --> 00:20:35,155
You're welcome! Oh!

232
00:20:35,238 --> 00:20:37,866
The thanklessness! What an accusation!

233
00:20:37,949 --> 00:20:40,785
I am gone! I will send you my bill!

234
00:21:01,639 --> 00:21:03,224
Ahsoka.

235
00:21:03,308 --> 00:21:04,976
It's good to see you are all safe.

236
00:21:05,059 --> 00:21:08,730
Yes, Master.
We had quite an eventful mission.

237
00:21:08,813 --> 00:21:09,898
The most eventful

238
00:21:09,981 --> 00:21:14,277
since the time Master Yoda
went to find his lightsaber crystal.

239
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,653
What?

240
00:21:15,737 --> 00:21:17,906
-Oh... Tell us!
-What happened then?

241
00:21:18,031 --> 00:21:21,367
I'm afraid that story will have to wait.

242
00:21:21,409 --> 00:21:22,911
For now, be proud.

243
00:21:23,036 --> 00:21:26,080
You have survived an ordeal
few your age could.

244
00:21:28,249 --> 00:21:30,877
Welcome home, young Jedi.

245
00:21:30,901 --> 00:21:35,901
http://hiqve.com/

